div1.p:




     ELIJAH BROWNING
(Policeman, H 132). I produce a certificate (Read;—"Central Criminal Court, June, 1858; 



     Thomas Simmonds Convicted of breaking and entering a warehouse, and ordered to be confined one year"). I would not swear that the prisoner is the man—I said at Worship-street that he was, but since then I have seen another man who I believe was the man convicted.
